Defines an attachment point on a [https://pz-wiki-modding.github.io/PZ-API-Docs/scripts/model.html model] or [https://pz-wiki-modding.github.io/PZ-API-Docs/scripts/vehicle.html vehicle] block. The ID is the attachment name, it can be a custom ID or an existing one often used to define specific attachments. While manually modifying the attachment block is definitely possible, it is recommended to use the [[Attachment_Editor|attachment editor]] to create and edit those attachments.

The syntax of this block should be as follows:
{{CodeSnip
| lang = cpp
| code = 
model upperScriptDefinition
{
    ...
    attachment attachmentPointName
    {
        ...
    }
    ...
}
}}

For example:
{{CodeSnip
| lang = cpp
| code = 
model Burger
{
    mesh = Burger,

    attachment Bip01_Prop2
    {
        offset = 0.0142 0.0401 0.0000,
        rotate = -23.3606 21.2788 37.5386,
        scale = 0.8280,
    }
}
}}

For a full list of attachment points, see [[Attachment_(scripts)#Attachment_Points|attachment]].

== Parameters ==
You can find a full list of the parameters in the [https://pz-wiki-modding.github.io/PZ-API-Docs/scripts/attachment.html ScriptsDocs].

